ROBERT H. EPPS v. WILLIAM RAINEY. [No. 32,

October Term, 1935.]

Decided December 4th, 1935.

The cause was submitted on briefs to Bond, C. J., Urner, Offutt, Parke, Sloan, Mitchell, Shehan, and Johnson, JJ.

Charles Jackson, Joseph O. Buchoff, Abraham Rostov, and Mark Jacks on,.tor the appellant. Benjamin Goldman, W. Albert Menchine, and L. Wether ed Barroll, for the appellee. Urner, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
